# ============================================================================
#  slacker — package source policy   (freezes + pins)
# ============================================================================
#
#  One rule per line. This file controls two opposite things:
#
#  1) FREEZE — slacker must never install, upgrade or remove the package.
#       name           freeze by exact name or substring/regex (matched on the
#                      package id, e.g.  firefox  or  xf86-.*-202.*)
#       series/        freeze a whole series — note the trailing slash (kde/, ap/)
#       @repo name     freeze only while the package's source IS that repo; it
#                      still accepts updates from OTHER repos per priority
#     Examples:
#       firefox
#       xf86-.*-202.*
#       kde/
#       @alienbob vlc
#
#  2) PIN — take a package ONLY from one repo, ignoring priority (the opposite
#     of a freeze). Easiest via the commands:
#       slacker pin alienbob:vlc      # vlc now comes only from alienbob
#       slacker unpin vlc             # back to normal priority resolution
#     ...or write it by hand with the 100% marker:
#       @repo 100% name
#     Example — vlc always from alienbob, even if a higher-priority repo has it:
#       @alienbob 100% vlc
#
#  Notes
#    * A FREEZE on a package always WINS over a PIN on the same package.
#    * Comments start with '#'; blank lines are ignored.
#    * Manage freezes with:  slacker frozen RULE...  /  slacker unfrozen RULE...
#    * Manage pins with:     slacker pin repo:pkg    /  slacker unpin pkg
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Examples (commented out — uncomment or use the commands above)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#firefox
#kde/
#@alienbob vlc
#@alienbob 100% vlc
